A Federal High Court 1, sitting in Ibadan, Oyo State, Wednesday, convicted and sentenced two internet fraudsters to prison after finding them guilty of criminal charges. DAILY POST learnt the suit was filed against the duo by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, EFCC, Ibadan zonal office. EFCC spokesman, Wilson Uwujaren, said this in a statement in Abuja. Further, it was explained that Onifade Gideon Idowu and Akinjobi Mumeen were arraigned on an amended charge following plea bargain agreement with the Commission. Also, the convicts were brought before the court on a one-count amended charge bordering on fraudulent impersonation, contrary to Section 22(2)(b)(i) of the Cybercrimes (Prohibition, Prevention etc.) Act, 2015 and punishable under Section 22(2)(b)(iv) of the same Act. But they pleaded guilty to their respective charges. Consequent upon the guilty plea, prosecution counsel, Murtala Sa’id Usman, prayed the court to sentence them according to the terms of the plea bargain agreement. In her ruling, Presiding Justice Patricia Ajoku found them guilty as charged and sentenced them to six months in prison each. She also ordered that the convicts would forfeit all items recovered from them during the course of investigation. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.